# ⚙️ Security Automation Pipeline

An end-to-end CI/CD security pipeline that automates log collection, alert generation, and configuration enforcement — reducing manual security operations overhead through infrastructure-as-code and event-driven automation.

---

## 📌 Overview

Manual security operations don't scale. This project builds a fully automated pipeline that continuously collects logs, enforces hardened configurations across hosts, and triggers alerts on anomalous activity — all wired together through a CI/CD workflow with Jenkins, Ansible, and Python.

**Think of it as a lightweight, self-hosted SecOps automation framework.**

---

## 🎯 Key Features

- 📥 **Centralized log collection** — rsyslog aggregates logs from multiple Linux hosts
- 🔔 **Automated alerting** — Python scripts parse logs and trigger alerts on defined patterns
- 🔧 **Configuration enforcement** — Ansible playbooks ensure hosts stay hardened on every run
- 🔄 **CI/CD integration** — Jenkins pipeline triggers security checks on code/config changes
- 🐳 **Containerized** — Docker used to isolate and deploy pipeline components

